This paper involves the development of a neural model based on a CNN-LSTM architecture that learns to detect Alzheimer's disease and related dementias using conversational transcripts. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of targeted features for dementia detection, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
